<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFEE3936EBD2C52BFA6259B5" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEE3936EBD2C52BFEA35904" blockId="64.[227,348,536,562]" box="[227,348,536,562]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<heading id="5A24A609FFEE3936EBD2C52BFEA35904" bold="true" box="[227,348,536,562]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFEE3936EBD2C52BFEA35904" bold="true" box="[227,348,536,562]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFEE3936EBD2C574FA6259B5" blockId="64.[227,1437,582,644]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">OL/OH = 1.63. Pyriform otoliths with large rostrum curving towards outer face at anterior tip. Sulcus wide, oblong. Ostium opens widely anteriorly. Cristae in cauda ridge-like, curving ventrally at posterior.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
